    "A well-trained AI model that can predict disease progression may have the potential to replace the placebo control group in clinical trials (Lee and Lee 2020), which can mitigate ethical concerns and improve the accuracy of clinical trial results.",
    "Recently, Insilico Medicine has introduced an AI platform called inClinico (https:// insil ico.",
    "com/ incli nico) to predict the success rate of clinical trials.",
    "It can also suggest alternative trial designs to improve the success rate of the clinical trial.",
    "Although AI has many potential advantages in clinical trials, there are significant risks to patients and liability concerns if the AI predictions (in data analysis, real-time monitoring, or any other application) are inaccurate."
